---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Home, ChevronRight, Scale, Eye, Code, Database, FileText, ExternalLink } from "@lucide/astro";
---

<Layout title="About — audit.et">
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-12 pb-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm mb-8">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-eth-text-muted hover:text-eth-green transition-colors">
        <Home class="w-3.5 h-3.5" />
        Home
      </a>
      <ChevronRight class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-eth-text-muted/50" />
      <span class="text-eth-text font-medium">About</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-eth-text mb-2">
      About audit.et
    </h1>
    <p class="text-eth-text-muted mb-10 max-w-2xl">
      An independent civic project making public audit data accessible and understandable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mb-12">
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-eth-green/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <Eye class="w-5 h-5 text-eth-green" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-eth-text mb-2">Transparency</h3>
        <p class="text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Public enterprises manage billions in public resources. Citizens deserve clear, accessible insight into how these funds are used and audited.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-eth-green/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <Scale class="w-5 h-5 text-eth-green" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-eth-text mb-2">Accountability</h3>
        <p class="text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          By visualizing audit opinions, financial trends, and key findings, we help highlight where accountability is strong and where questions remain.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-eth-green/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <Code class="w-5 h-5 text-eth-green" />
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-eth-text mb-2">Open Source</h3>
        <p class="text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          This entire project is open source. The code, the data extraction, and the visualizations are all publicly available for anyone to inspect, contribute to, or build upon.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is this -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mb-12">
    <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-eth-text mb-4">What is audit.et?</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-eth-text">audit.et</strong> (ኦዲት) is an independent civic project that takes publicly available audit reports from Ethiopian state-owned enterprises and transforms them into interactive visualizations and structured data.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ethiopia's state-owned enterprises, many now under <strong class="text-eth-text">Ethiopian Investment Holdings (EIH)</strong>, manage significant national assets across energy, agriculture, logistics, and more. Their audit reports, published by the Office of the Federal Auditor General and Audit Service Corporation, contain critical financial data — but they are often locked in PDF documents that are difficult to analyze.
        </p>
        <p>
          This project extracts that data into structured JSON, normalizes it across different reporting formats and fiscal years, and presents it through charts, tables, and summary statistics that anyone can understand.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-eth-text mb-6">How It Works</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-eth-green text-white flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold mb-4">1</div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <FileText class="w-4 h-4 text-eth-gold" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-eth-text text-sm">Extract</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Audit reports (PDFs) from the Federal Auditor General are parsed and extracted into structured JSON data files.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-eth-green text-white flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold mb-4">2</div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <Database class="w-4 h-4 text-eth-gold" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-eth-text text-sm">Normalize</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Data is normalized across different schemas, reporting formats, and calendar systems (Ethiopian vs Gregorian) into a consistent format.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-eth-green text-white flex items-center justify-center font-mono text-sm font-bold mb-4">3</div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
          <Eye class="w-4 h-4 text-eth-gold" />
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-eth-text text-sm">Visualize</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-eth-text-dim text-sm leading-relaxed">
          The normalized data is rendered as interactive charts, tables, and summary statistics at build time — no server required.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Data sources & disclaimer -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mb-12">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-eth-card border border-eth-card-border rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-eth-text mb-3">Data Sources</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-eth-text-dim">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <ExternalLink class="w-4 h-4 text-eth-gold shrink-0 mt-0.5" />
            <span>Office of the Federal Auditor General (OFAG) — published audit reports</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <ExternalLink class="w-4 h-4 text-eth-gold shrink-0 mt-0.5" />
            <span>Audit Service Corporation (ASC) — independent audits of state enterprises</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <ExternalLink class="w-4 h-4 text-eth-gold shrink-0 mt-0.5" />
            <span>Publicly available financial statements and annual reports</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-eth-gold-light border border-eth-gold/20 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-eth-text mb-3">Disclaimer</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-eth-text-dim leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            This is an <strong class="text-eth-text">independent, unofficial project</strong>. It is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Ethiopian government, Ethiopian Investment Holdings (EIH), or any political party.
          </p>
          <p>
            The data is provided as-is for informational purposes. While we strive for accuracy, we cannot guarantee that all information is complete or error-free. Financial figures are extracted from published audit reports and may be subject to OCR or interpretation errors.
          </p>
          <p>
            Ethiopian fiscal years end on Hamle 30 (July 7 in the Gregorian calendar). All currency figures are in Ethiopian Birr (ETB).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
